235
00:18:49,011 --> 00:18:50,575
<b>Yes.</b>

236
00:18:50,646 --> 00:18:53,145
<b>This means everything to me.</b>

237
00:18:56,252 --> 00:18:58,015
<b>"'Yes, ' he said."</b>

238
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:14,465
<b>("All My Firsts", A Novel by Cha Yun Taek)</b>

239
00:19:25,181 --> 00:19:30,545
<b>(To my love)</b>

240
00:19:36,492 --> 00:19:40,355
<b>"He lowered his head, looking embarrassed."</b>

241
00:19:45,467 --> 00:19:49,165
<b>"I burst into tears."</b>

242
00:20:13,095 --> 00:20:14,590
<b>Welcome.</b>

243
00:20:14,597 --> 00:20:16,225
<b>Come on in.</b>

244
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:23,695
<b>Thanks for coming all the way here.</b>

245
00:20:30,746 --> 00:20:32,640
<b>We could have talked on the phone.</b>

246
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:36,350
<b>I thought it'd be better to talk in person.</b>

247
00:20:36,352 --> 00:20:38,015
<b>Well...</b>

248
00:20:38,087 --> 00:20:42,920
<b>Apparently, my daughter happened to pass by your bookstore recently.</b>

249
00:20:42,925 --> 00:20:46,820
<b>She says your bookstore is doing very well...</b>

250
00:20:46,829 --> 00:20:51,925
<b>and we shouldn't have given away that house to you.</b>

251
00:20:54,536 --> 00:20:56,370
<b>We recently held a public event,</b>

252
00:20:56,372 --> 00:20:58,770
<b>and it attracted quite a few people.</b>

253
00:20:58,774 --> 00:21:00,700
<b>That must have given her the wrong idea.</b>

254
00:21:00,709 --> 00:21:02,570
<b>If you're unhappy with the situation,</b>

255
00:21:02,578 --> 00:21:06,410
<b>I'll start paying rent this month.</b>

256
00:21:06,415 --> 00:21:08,005
<b>Forget it.</b>

257
00:21:10,419 --> 00:21:13,445
<b>Come with me to my study.</b>

258
00:21:13,589 --> 00:21:15,155
<b>Pardon?</b>

259
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:18,494
<b>If you're unhappy with the situation,</b>

260
00:21:18,494 --> 00:21:22,631
<b>I'll start paying rent this month.</b>

261
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:24,466
<b>Forget it.</b>

262
00:21:26,935 --> 00:21:29,938
<b>Come with me to my study.</b>

263
00:21:29,938 --> 00:21:32,308
<b>- Pardon? - Come on.</b>

264
00:21:41,984 --> 00:21:44,186
<b>I knew he'd do that.</b>

265
00:21:45,421 --> 00:21:47,456
<b>He wants to show off.</b>

266
00:21:47,523 --> 00:21:49,024
<b>Show off what?</b>

267
00:21:49,024 --> 00:21:50,826
<b>His books.</b>

268
00:21:51,527 --> 00:21:55,064
<b>Since he heard that the young man from the bookstore was coming over,</b>

269
00:21:55,064 --> 00:21:58,467
<b>he has been organizing his antique books all day.</b>

270
00:21:59,268 --> 00:22:01,036
<b>I see.</b>

271
00:22:09,044 --> 00:22:11,146
<b>Does someone play the piano?</b>

272
00:22:11,146 --> 00:22:12,715
<b>Yes.</b>

273
00:22:13,048 --> 00:22:14,416
<b>I do.</b>

274
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:15,617
<b>Really?</b>

275
00:22:15,617 --> 00:22:17,720
<b>I recently started.</b>

276
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:19,521
<b>It's quite fun.</b>

277
00:22:19,521 --> 00:22:21,090
<b>I see.</b>

278
00:22:31,967 --> 00:22:36,705
<b>Are you familiar with "Deer", a collection of poems by Baek Seok?</b>

279
00:22:37,673 --> 00:22:39,007
<b>Yes.</b>

280
00:22:39,007 --> 00:22:42,644
<b>Only 100 copies were ever printed,</b>

281
00:22:42,644 --> 00:22:44,613
<b>so they were very rare.</b>

282
00:22:45,414 --> 00:22:47,649
<b>("Deer", Baek Seok)</b>

283
00:22:47,649 --> 00:22:49,284
<b>Is this...</b>

284
00:22:49,585 --> 00:22:52,488
<b>Even the poet Yun Dong Ju failed to get his hands on it...</b>

285
00:22:52,488 --> 00:22:54,790
<b>and had to transcribe it by hand.</b>

286
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:56,592
<b>How did you...</b>

287
00:22:56,925 --> 00:22:58,627
<b>I have my ways.</b>

288
00:23:00,863 --> 00:23:02,931
<b>It might just be an unofficial copy.</b>

289
00:23:02,931 --> 00:23:05,667
<b>Still, it made me so happy. I couldn't put it down for a while.</b>

290
00:23:16,211 --> 00:23:18,147
<b>(A Pitch-dark Night)</b>

291
00:23:18,147 --> 00:23:20,215
<b>"The lights in the room are out."</b>

292
00:23:20,616 --> 00:23:23,185
<b>"The white clothes hanging from the rack..."</b>

293
00:23:24,119 --> 00:23:26,889
<b>"look distant and cold."</b>

294
00:23:27,289 --> 00:23:30,926
<b>"I hear the sound of horse bells from the northwest."</b>

295
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:35,597
<b>"I open the door. The night sky is pitch-dark."</b>

296
00:23:36,532 --> 00:23:39,368
<b>"There is a scent of pine mushrooms in the air."</b>

297
00:23:39,501 --> 00:23:41,637
<b>Don't worry about...</b>

298
00:23:41,637 --> 00:23:43,806
<b>what my daughter said.</b>

299
00:23:46,175 --> 00:23:47,342
<b>Still...</b>

300
00:23:47,342 --> 00:23:50,012
<b>I'm glad you turned the house I abandoned...</b>

301
00:23:50,012 --> 00:23:52,748
<b>into a bookstore.</b>

302
00:23:52,915 --> 00:23:54,149
<b>Yes, but...</b>

303
00:23:54,149 --> 00:23:56,652
<b>I raised her with love.</b>

304
00:23:57,119 --> 00:24:00,222
<b>But that doesn't mean a thing once money is involved.</b>

305
00:24:01,790 --> 00:24:04,626
<b>Everything in the world changes.</b>

306
00:24:04,626 --> 00:24:07,062
<b>Everything changes and leaves.</b>

307
00:24:07,062 --> 00:24:09,198
<b>Your children are no exception.</b>

308
00:24:11,834 --> 00:24:13,735
<b>But books are different.</b>

309
00:24:13,735 --> 00:24:16,438
<b>While containing so much,</b>

310
00:24:16,438 --> 00:24:19,007
<b>they rarely change.</b>

311
00:24:23,579 --> 00:24:26,548
<b>Keep your bookstore going.</b>

312
00:24:35,624 --> 00:24:38,126
<b>I told you from the start you could do whatever with the house...</b>

313
00:24:38,126 --> 00:24:39,928
<b>as long as you use it as a bookstore.</b>

314
00:24:41,163 --> 00:24:42,731
<b>Yes.</b>

315
00:25:10,692 --> 00:25:13,128
<b>That's right.</b>

316
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:32,080
<b>- I had a great time today. - Oh, me too.</b>

317
00:25:32,147 --> 00:25:33,615
<b>Where are you headed too?</b>

318
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:35,617
<b>I have to get back to work.</b>

319
00:25:35,617 --> 00:25:38,520
<b>- I see. - Don't forget to have lunch.</b>

320
00:25:38,520 --> 00:25:41,957
<b>- We can see each other again. - Okay, I'll see you later.</b>

321
00:25:41,957 --> 00:25:43,525
<b>Okay.</b>

322
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:47,529
<b>- Have a good day. - Goodbye.</b>

323
00:25:55,737 --> 00:25:58,640
<b>Well, well. Hello there, my friend.</b>

324
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:01,109
<b>My friend who is older than me.</b>

325
00:26:01,109 --> 00:26:04,212
<b>- What? - What were you doing just now?</b>

326
00:26:04,212 --> 00:26:05,280
<b>What do you mean? Why?</b>

327
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:07,416
<b>I knew you'd deny it.</b>

328
00:26:07,416 --> 00:26:09,751
<b>What? Deny what?</b>

329
00:26:10,352 --> 00:26:13,322
<b>Will you still deny it after seeing this?</b>

330
00:26:13,322 --> 00:26:14,923
<b>Say something, my friend.</b>

331
00:26:14,923 --> 00:26:17,759
<b>My friend who is much older than me.</b>

332
00:26:17,759 --> 00:26:19,561
<b>Well, Hwi...</b>

333
00:26:19,995 --> 00:26:21,396
<b>I was just briefly saying hi.</b>

334
00:26:21,396 --> 00:26:23,599
<b>- Is that so? - Yes.</b>

335
00:26:23,599 --> 00:26:25,334
<b>I bumped into an old friend of mine.</b>

336
00:26:25,334 --> 00:26:28,971
<b>Oh, so if you bump into an old friend on the street,</b>

337
00:26:28,971 --> 00:26:31,206
<b>you smile warmly with a bashful look...</b>

338
00:26:31,206 --> 00:26:32,874
<b>and shake their hand?</b>

339
00:26:32,874 --> 00:26:36,178
<b>Jang Woo, I didn't know that about you.</b>

340
00:26:36,912 --> 00:26:39,047
<b>Just give me that.</b>

341
00:26:41,850 --> 00:26:43,151
<b>How...</b>

342
00:26:43,151 --> 00:26:46,254
<b>How could you be so mean?</b>

343
00:26:46,254 --> 00:26:48,457
<b>You're not like your brother at all.</b>

344
00:26:48,457 --> 00:26:49,958
<b>You're quick to catch on.</b>

345
00:26:49,958 --> 00:26:52,694
<b>Unlike Eun Seop, you know.</b>

346
00:26:56,098 --> 00:26:58,133
<b>Come on, my friend.</b>

347
00:26:58,133 --> 00:27:00,435
<b>I even pay 10 dollars for information...</b>

348
00:27:00,435 --> 00:27:03,005
<b>Kwon Hyun Ji brings me.</b>

349
00:27:03,972 --> 00:27:06,108
<b>Goodness, seriously.</b>

350
00:27:12,347 --> 00:27:15,117
<b>Gosh, Jang Woo. I was just asking for 10 bucks.</b>

351
00:27:15,117 --> 00:27:16,218
<b>Thank you!</b>

352
00:27:16,218 --> 00:27:19,488
<b>Thank you, and I'll treat you like my brother for the next few days.</b>

353
00:27:19,488 --> 00:27:21,423
<b>That's gross, so just call me Jang Woo.</b>

354
00:27:21,423 --> 00:27:23,291
<b>Really? Send!</b>

355
00:27:23,291 --> 00:27:25,394
<b>No, don't send it...</b>

356
00:27:25,394 --> 00:27:28,363
<b>I'll be really grateful if you delete that.</b>

357
00:27:28,363 --> 00:27:31,133
<b>Shall I delete it then?</b>

358
00:27:31,133 --> 00:27:32,567
<b>How could you...</b>

359
00:27:32,567 --> 00:27:33,702
<b>Why aren't you at school?</b>

360
00:27:33,702 --> 00:27:35,637
<b>It's lunchtime, so I'm taking a stroll.</b>

361
00:27:35,637 --> 00:27:37,706
<b>You should be in the cafeteria eating lunch then.</b>

362
00:27:37,706 --> 00:27:39,541
<b>Come on, you weren't eating at work either...</b>

363
00:27:39,541 --> 00:27:41,743
<b>and wearing that goofy smile over here.</b>

364
00:27:41,743 --> 00:27:43,345
<b>That's because I came here briefly for lunch...</b>

365
00:27:43,345 --> 00:27:44,713
<b>So you know it's the same thing, my friend.</b>

366
00:27:44,713 --> 00:27:47,716
<b>My friend who is much older than me.</b>

367
00:27:47,716 --> 00:27:49,685
<b>Well, I should get going since I'm busy.</b>

368
00:27:49,685 --> 00:27:51,319
<b>Take care, my friend. Bye.</b>

369
00:27:51,319 --> 00:27:53,989
<b>Hurry up and go. Get going.</b>

370
00:28:00,696 --> 00:28:02,297
<b>Didn't you...</b>

371
00:28:02,464 --> 00:28:04,299
<b>just tell me to go?</b>

372
00:28:04,299 --> 00:28:08,336
<b>Oh, I was telling you to drop me off at school and go.</b>

373
00:28:08,937 --> 00:28:11,173
<b>Jang Woo, I'm in a hurry, so let's go.</b>

374
00:28:11,173 --> 00:28:14,342
<b>My lunchtime is almost over. Or maybe it's already over.</b>

375
00:28:14,342 --> 00:28:16,011
<b>Do you want to see me receive penalty points?</b>

376
00:28:16,011 --> 00:28:17,846
<b>Do you know how many penalty points I received lately...</b>

377
00:28:17,846 --> 00:28:19,548
<b>because of Eun Seop's "The Catcher in the Rye"?</b>

378
00:28:19,548 --> 00:28:21,149
<b>Let's go then.</b>

379
00:28:23,118 --> 00:28:24,886
<b>I don't have much time either.</b>

380
00:28:24,886 --> 00:28:26,888
<b>Let's go, my friend.</b>

381
00:28:26,888 --> 00:28:28,590
<b>Hwi, why are you so heavy?</b>

382
00:28:28,590 --> 00:28:30,625
<b>Just keep pedaling, my friend.</b>

383
00:28:30,625 --> 00:28:33,495
<b>Why do you have such weak legs for a man?</b>

384
00:28:40,936 --> 00:28:43,138
<b>You know that day...</b>

385
00:28:44,206 --> 00:28:45,874
<b>The day...</b>

386
00:28:46,475 --> 00:28:49,611
<b>when I got on the Mugunghwa train.</b>

387
00:28:58,620 --> 00:29:01,623
<b>I really wanted to die that day.</b>

388
00:29:05,761 --> 00:29:08,563
<b>That's how I felt back then.</b>

389
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:20,142
<b>(A murderer's daughter sits here.)</b>

390
00:29:20,142 --> 00:29:22,177
<b>Waking up in the morning and going to school...</b>

391
00:29:22,177 --> 00:29:24,379
<b>felt so miserable back then.</b>

392
00:29:24,379 --> 00:29:25,914
<b>- Hey. - Come on.</b>

393
00:29:25,914 --> 00:29:28,950
<b>I was pondering how I should die...</b>

394
00:29:32,454 --> 00:29:34,022
<b>And then...</b>

395
00:29:34,022 --> 00:29:36,591
<b>I decided to go to a station near a river.</b>

396
00:29:36,691 --> 00:29:39,795
<b>I was going to go there and die.</b>

397
00:30:06,154 --> 00:30:07,455
<b>But...</b>

398
00:30:07,455 --> 00:30:10,792
<b>it felt like I wouldn't die if I just walked in.</b>

399
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:14,729
<b>I was thinking if I should put some rocks...</b>

400
00:30:14,729 --> 00:30:17,599
<b>inside my pockets.</b>

401
00:30:19,701 --> 00:30:22,003
<b>But I suddenly felt so hungry.</b>

402
00:30:25,207 --> 00:30:29,811
<b>Fine. Then shall I eat one last meal before dying?</b>

403
00:31:32,307 --> 00:31:35,343
<b>But after I finished eating,</b>

404
00:31:35,343 --> 00:31:37,012
<b>I felt sleepy.</b>

405
00:31:55,897 --> 00:31:58,633
<b>Then shall I take a quick nap?</b>

406
00:32:22,023 --> 00:32:24,159
<b>The whole day went by like that...</b>

407
00:32:24,159 --> 00:32:26,394
<b>and something came to mind.</b>

408
00:32:27,762 --> 00:32:32,200
<b>Right, I'll never die at this rate.</b>

409
00:32:35,804 --> 00:32:37,439
<b>No.</b>

410
00:32:37,939 --> 00:32:40,175
<b>I must die.</b>

411
00:32:45,347 --> 00:32:47,749
<b>I must die. I'll die...</b>

412
00:32:47,916 --> 00:32:51,987
<b>and make everyone who bullied me regret it.</b>

413
00:33:26,287 --> 00:33:28,523
<b>Hey, Mok Hae Won!</b>

414
00:33:28,890 --> 00:33:30,625
<b>Mok Hae Won!</b>

415
00:33:30,625 --> 00:33:32,794
<b>Come back!</b>

416
00:33:34,062 --> 00:33:35,764
<b>Mok Hae Won!</b>

417
00:33:37,866 --> 00:33:39,534
<b>Mok Hae Won!</b>

418
00:33:40,502 --> 00:33:42,203
<b>Ouch, that hurts.</b>

419
00:33:42,203 --> 00:33:43,405
<b>Hey, Mok Hae Won!</b>

420
00:33:43,405 --> 00:33:46,708
<b>You brat! Hey, Mok Hae Won!</b>

421
00:33:46,708 --> 00:33:48,343
<b>How did...</b>

422
00:33:50,078 --> 00:33:51,346
<b>Mok Hae Won.</b>

423
00:33:51,346 --> 00:33:53,581
<b>It still puzzles me.</b>

424
00:33:53,915 --> 00:33:57,318
<b>How did my aunt know I was there?</b>

425
00:33:59,687 --> 00:34:02,223
<b>Is that why you decided not to die?</b>

426
00:34:02,223 --> 00:34:03,792
<b>Yes.</b>

427
00:34:10,198 --> 00:34:12,400
<b>If you want to die,</b>

428
00:34:15,537 --> 00:34:17,906
<b>I will die with you.</b>

429
00:34:21,209 --> 00:34:22,944
<b>What are you saying?</b>

430
00:34:25,747 --> 00:34:28,049
<b>Let's die together. My mom is dead too anyway.</b>

431
00:34:28,049 --> 00:34:30,185
<b>Come on, seriously.</b>

432
00:34:31,186 --> 00:34:34,189
<b>Why? Are you scared?</b>

433
00:34:44,232 --> 00:34:48,336
<b>The thought of wanting to die suddenly vanished.</b>

434
00:34:51,005 --> 00:34:52,273
<b>It felt like...</b>

435
00:34:52,273 --> 00:34:55,910
<b>my aunt would keep nagging me even when I was dying.</b>

436
00:35:00,915 --> 00:35:03,084
<b>I'm glad you lived.</b>

437
00:35:08,823 --> 00:35:13,027
<b>Thank you for not dying, Hae Won.</b>

438
00:35:20,969 --> 00:35:22,770
<b>Tell me.</b>

439
00:35:26,407 --> 00:35:28,343
<b>Tell me, Eun Seop.</b>

440
00:35:29,210 --> 00:35:30,778
<b>Tell you what?</b>

441
00:35:31,646 --> 00:35:33,448
<b>About us.</b>

442
00:35:39,454 --> 00:35:41,156
<b>Is this love?</b>

443
00:35:49,063 --> 00:35:50,865
<b>I want to hear your answer.</b>

444
00:35:52,367 --> 00:35:54,135
<b>Is this love?</b>

445
00:35:57,005 --> 00:35:58,573
<b>Yes.</b>

446
00:35:59,908 --> 00:36:01,576
<b>It is love.</b>

447
00:36:06,915 --> 00:36:08,483
<b>I feel the same way.</b>

448
00:36:31,339 --> 00:36:35,877
<b>(Hodu House)</b>

449
00:36:46,321 --> 00:36:49,157
<b>Gosh, you scared me.</b>

450
00:36:50,191 --> 00:36:51,759
<b>What's up?</b>

451
00:36:52,493 --> 00:36:55,964
<b>Hey, how much of the novel have you written so far?</b>

452
00:36:56,731 --> 00:36:57,865
<b>What is this about?</b>

453
00:36:57,865 --> 00:36:59,734
<b>How much have you written so far?</b>

454
00:36:59,734 --> 00:37:02,270
<b>Look, mister.</b>

455
00:37:02,270 --> 00:37:04,505
<b>It hasn't even been three days yet.</b>

456
00:37:04,505 --> 00:37:07,508
<b>Hey, what kind of crazy chief editor...</b>

457
00:37:07,508 --> 00:37:09,510
<b>shows up at an author's place and harasses her...</b>

458
00:37:09,510 --> 00:37:11,412
<b>just a couple of days after signing a contract with her?</b>

459
00:37:11,412 --> 00:37:13,047
<b>Are you losing your mind?</b>

460
00:37:13,047 --> 00:37:14,649
<b>You must have the opening sentence figured out.</b>

461
00:37:14,649 --> 00:37:16,818
<b>Oh, the opening sentence?</b>

462
00:37:16,818 --> 00:37:18,052
<b>You have it, right?</b>

463
00:37:18,052 --> 00:37:21,356
<b>The opening sentence... I did write something.</b>

464
00:37:21,356 --> 00:37:23,791
<b>Don't tell me you came all the way here to talk to me about that.</b>

465
00:37:23,791 --> 00:37:27,061
<b>I sure did. I came all the way here to talk to you about it.</b>

466
00:37:27,462 --> 00:37:29,163
<b>You must have a lot of time on your hands, Crybaby.</b>

467
00:37:29,163 --> 00:37:32,033
